Note:
This file implements x86_64 peephole optimization passes for the Runa compiler backend.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Eliminate redundant MOV instructions (self-moves)
- Strength-reduce IMUL by powers of two into SHL instructions
- Optimize zeroing patterns (MOV $0 into XOR self)
- Convert ADD/SUB by 1 into INC/DEC instructions
- Eliminate dead stores (consecutive writes to the same register)
- Thread jump chains to bypass trivial intermediate blocks
- Fold constant arithmetic operations at compile time
- Remove NOP instructions and renumber instruction indices

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Peephole optimizations reduce instruction count and improve pipeline throughput
- Strength reduction eliminates expensive multiply instructions where shifts suffice
- Jump threading eliminates unnecessary control flow indirection
- Constant folding evaluates compile-time-known arithmetic at compile time
- NOP removal produces compact final instruction streams

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- run_x86_64_peephole: Main entry point orchestrating all optimization passes
- eliminate_redundant_moves: Removes MOV reg, reg where source equals destination
- strength_reduce_multiply: Replaces IMUL by power-of-2 with SHL
- optimize_zeroing: Replaces MOV $0, reg with XOR reg, reg
- optimize_inc_dec: Replaces ADD/SUB $1 with INC/DEC and ADD/SUB $-1 with DEC/INC
- eliminate_dead_stores: Removes writes overwritten without intervening reads
- thread_jumps: Redirects jumps through trivial forwarding blocks
- fold_constant_operations: Evaluates constant arithmetic at compile time
- remove_nops: Final cleanup removing NOP instructions and renumbering indices
- is_power_of_two: Helper testing if a value has exactly one set bit
- log2_of_power: Helper computing the bit position of the single set bit

Dependencies:
- Imports LIR core types for opcode constants, register constants, and type sizes
- Imports LIR node definitions for instruction and operand memory layouts
- Imports memory/layout for OWNED HEAP allocation (Tier 3)
- Imports collections/list for instruction list management
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/lir/lir.runa" as LIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/lir/lir_nodes.runa" as LIRNodes
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

