Note: ============================================================================
Note: OptimizationStats Type
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Tracks the number of optimizations applied by each individual pass during a
single invocation of the peephole optimizer. This provides visibility into which
passes are most effective and allows callers to detect when the optimizer has
reached a fixed point (no more optimizations possible).

The stats structure is allocated on the owned heap (Tier 3) because it persists
beyond the optimizer call and is returned to the caller.

Layout (10 fields * 8 bytes = 80 bytes):
  [0]  redundant_moves_eliminated
  [8]  strength_reductions_applied
  [16] zeroing_optimizations
  [24] inc_dec_optimizations
  [32] dead_stores_eliminated
  [40] jumps_threaded
  [48] constants_folded
  [56] nops_removed
  [64] total_optimizations
  [72] passes_run
@End Reasoning

Type called "OptimizationStats":
    redundant_moves_eliminated as Integer
    strength_reductions_applied as Integer
    zeroing_optimizations as Integer
    inc_dec_optimizations as Integer
    dead_stores_eliminated as Integer
    jumps_threaded as Integer
    constants_folded as Integer
    nops_removed as Integer
    total_optimizations as Integer
    passes_run as Integer
End Type

Constant STATS_REDUNDANT_MOVES as Integer is 0
Constant STATS_STRENGTH_REDUCTIONS as Integer is 8
Constant STATS_ZEROING as Integer is 16
Constant STATS_INC_DEC as Integer is 24
Constant STATS_DEAD_STORES as Integer is 32
Constant STATS_JUMPS_THREADED as Integer is 40
Constant STATS_CONSTANTS_FOLDED as Integer is 48
Constant STATS_NOPS_REMOVED as Integer is 56
Constant STATS_TOTAL as Integer is 64
Constant STATS_PASSES as Integer is 72
Constant STATS_SIZE as Integer is 80

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Helper Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Tests whether a given integer value is an exact power of two. A positive integer
is a power of two if and only if it has exactly one bit set in its binary
representation. The expression (value & (value - 1)) clears the lowest set bit;
if the result is zero and value is positive, then value had exactly one set bit.

Returns 1 if value > 0 and value is a power of two, 0 otherwise.
@End Reasoning

Process called "is_power_of_two" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: value & (value - 1) clears the lowest set bit
    Note: If the result is 0, value had exactly one bit set
    Let cleared be value & (value minus 1)
    If cleared equals 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Computes the base-2 logarithm for values that are exact powers of two. This is
equivalent to counting the number of trailing zero bits (the position of the
single set bit). The function shifts right repeatedly until the value reaches 1,
counting iterations.

Precondition: value must be a positive power of two. If value is not a power of
two, the result is the floor of log2(value).
@End Reasoning

Process called "log2_of_power" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let shift_count be 0
    Let v be value

    While v is greater than 1:
        Let v be v divided by 2
        Let shift_count be shift_count plus 1
    End While

    Return shift_count
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper to create an OptimizationStats structure on the owned heap, with all
counters initialized to zero.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_stats" returns Integer:
    Let stats be Layout.allocate(STATS_SIZE)
    If stats equals 0:
        Display "create_stats: allocation failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    __store(stats, STATS_REDUNDANT_MOVES, 0)
    __store(stats, STATS_STRENGTH_REDUCTIONS, 0)
    __store(stats, STATS_ZEROING, 0)
    __store(stats, STATS_INC_DEC, 0)
    __store(stats, STATS_DEAD_STORES, 0)
    __store(stats, STATS_JUMPS_THREADED, 0)
    __store(stats, STATS_CONSTANTS_FOLDED, 0)
    __store(stats, STATS_NOPS_REMOVED, 0)
    __store(stats, STATS_TOTAL, 0)
    __store(stats, STATS_PASSES, 0)

    Return stats
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper to check whether an instruction opcode produces a register write. This is
used by dead store elimination to determine if an instruction defines a value in
its result operand. Data movement and arithmetic instructions all write their
result register.
@End Reasoning

Process called "instruction_writes_register" that takes opcode as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Data movement
    If opcode equals LIR_MOV:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Arithmetic operations
    If opcode equals LIR_ADD:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode equals LIR_SUB:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode equals LIR_IMUL:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode equals LIR_NEG:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode equals LIR_INC:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode equals LIR_DEC:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Logical operations
    If opcode equals LIR_AND:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode equals LIR_OR:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode equals LIR_XOR:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Shift operations
    If opcode equals LIR_SHL:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opcode equals LIR_SHR:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper to check whether an instruction reads from a given register. An
instruction reads a register if it appears as operand1 or operand2 (and those
operands are register-type operands with a matching register ID). This is used
by dead store elimination to determine whether a value is consumed between two
writes.
@End Reasoning

Process called "instruction_reads_register" that takes instr as Integer, reg_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If instr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check operand 1
    Let op1_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP1)
    If op1_ptr is not equal to 0:
        Let op1_type be __load(op1_ptr, OP_TYPE)
        If op1_type equals OPERAND_REGISTER:
            Let op1_reg be __load(op1_ptr, OP_REG_ID)
            If op1_reg equals reg_id:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Note: Memory operands can also read registers via base and index
        If op1_type equals OPERAND_MEMORY:
            Let op1_base be __load(op1_ptr, OP_BASE_REG)
            If op1_base equals reg_id:
                Return 1
            End If
            Let op1_index be __load(op1_ptr, OP_INDEX_REG)
            If op1_index equals reg_id:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Check operand 2
    Let op2_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP2)
    If op2_ptr is not equal to 0:
        Let op2_type be __load(op2_ptr, OP_TYPE)
        If op2_type equals OPERAND_REGISTER:
            Let op2_reg be __load(op2_ptr, OP_REG_ID)
            If op2_reg equals reg_id:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        If op2_type equals OPERAND_MEMORY:
            Let op2_base be __load(op2_ptr, OP_BASE_REG)
            If op2_base equals reg_id:
                Return 1
            End If
            Let op2_index be __load(op2_ptr, OP_INDEX_REG)
            If op2_index equals reg_id:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Check operand 3
    Let op3_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP3)
    If op3_ptr is not equal to 0:
        Let op3_type be __load(op3_ptr, OP_TYPE)
        If op3_type equals OPERAND_REGISTER:
            Let op3_reg be __load(op3_ptr, OP_REG_ID)
            If op3_reg equals reg_id:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        If op3_type equals OPERAND_MEMORY:
            Let op3_base be __load(op3_ptr, OP_BASE_REG)
            If op3_base equals reg_id:
                Return 1
            End If
            Let op3_index be __load(op3_ptr, OP_INDEX_REG)
            If op3_index equals reg_id:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper to extract the destination register ID from an instruction's result
operand. Returns -1 if the instruction has no result operand or the result
is not a register operand.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_result_register" that takes instr as Integer returns Integer:
    If instr equals 0:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If

    Let result_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_RESULT)
    If result_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If

    Let result_type be __load(result_ptr, OP_TYPE)
    If result_type equals OPERAND_REGISTER:
        Return __load(result_ptr, OP_REG_ID)
    End If

    Return 0 minus 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
run_x86_64_peephole is the main entry point for x86_64 peephole optimizations.
It orchestrates all optimization passes in a specific order chosen for maximum
effectiveness:

1. eliminate_redundant_moves - Remove self-moves first (cheapest pass, clears noise)
2. strength_reduce_multiply - Replace IMUL with SHL where possible
3. optimize_zeroing - Replace MOV $0 with XOR (shorter encoding, dependency break)
4. optimize_inc_dec - Replace ADD/SUB $1/$-1 with INC/DEC
5. fold_constant_operations - Evaluate constant arithmetic at compile time
6. eliminate_dead_stores - Remove writes with no readers (depends on prior passes)
7. thread_jumps - Redirect through trivial jump blocks
8. remove_nops - Final cleanup, compact instruction lists

The passes are run in a single sequence. Redundant move elimination and constant
folding can create new NOP instructions, which are cleaned up by the final
remove_nops pass.

Returns a pointer to an OptimizationStats structure containing per-pass counts.
@End Reasoning

Process called "run_x86_64_peephole" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function equals 0:
        Display "run_x86_64_peephole: null function pointer"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let stats be create_stats()
    If stats equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Pass 1 - Eliminate redundant self-moves
    Let moves_eliminated be eliminate_redundant_moves(lir_function)
    __store(stats, STATS_REDUNDANT_MOVES, moves_eliminated)

    Note: Pass 2 - Strength-reduce multiplications by powers of two
    Let strength_reduced be strength_reduce_multiply(lir_function)
    __store(stats, STATS_STRENGTH_REDUCTIONS, strength_reduced)

    Note: Pass 3 - Optimize zeroing patterns
    Let zeroing_count be optimize_zeroing(lir_function)
    __store(stats, STATS_ZEROING, zeroing_count)

    Note: Pass 4 - Convert ADD/SUB $1 to INC/DEC
    Let inc_dec_count be optimize_inc_dec(lir_function)
    __store(stats, STATS_INC_DEC, inc_dec_count)

    Note: Pass 5 - Fold constant operations
    Let folded_count be fold_constant_operations(lir_function)
    __store(stats, STATS_CONSTANTS_FOLDED, folded_count)

    Note: Pass 6 - Eliminate dead stores
    Let dead_stores be eliminate_dead_stores(lir_function)
    __store(stats, STATS_DEAD_STORES, dead_stores)

    Note: Pass 7 - Thread jump chains
    Let threaded_count be thread_jumps(lir_function)
    __store(stats, STATS_JUMPS_THREADED, threaded_count)

    Note: Pass 8 - Remove NOP instructions (final cleanup)
    Let nops_removed be remove_nops(lir_function)
    __store(stats, STATS_NOPS_REMOVED, nops_removed)

    Note: Compute totals
    Let total be moves_eliminated plus strength_reduced plus zeroing_count plus inc_dec_count plus folded_count plus dead_stores plus threaded_count plus nops_removed
    __store(stats, STATS_TOTAL, total)
    __store(stats, STATS_PASSES, 8)

    Return stats
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pass 1: Eliminate Redundant Moves
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Scans every instruction in every basic block of the function. When a MOV
instruction is found where the source and destination are both register operands
with the same register ID, the instruction is replaced with NOP (opcode 30000).

This commonly arises after register allocation when a virtual register is
assigned to the same physical register as its source. The move becomes a no-op
and wastes a pipeline slot.

The instruction is converted in-place by overwriting the opcode field to LIR_NOP,
preserving all other fields for potential debugging use.

Returns the number of redundant moves eliminated.
@End Reasoning

Process called "eliminate_redundant_moves" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let eliminated_count be 0

    Note: Iterate over all basic blocks
    Let blocks_ptr be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCKS)
    Let block_count be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCK_COUNT)

    If blocks_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If block_count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_idx be 0
    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be List.list_get(blocks_ptr, block_idx)
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instr_list be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS)
            Let instr_count be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT)

            If instr_list is not equal to 0:
                Let instr_idx be 0
                While instr_idx is less than instr_count:
                    Let instr be List.list_get(instr_list, instr_idx)
                    If instr is not equal to 0:
                        Let opcode be __load(instr, INSTR_OPCODE)

                        If opcode equals LIR_MOV:
                            Note: Get result (destination) operand
                            Let result_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_RESULT)
                            Note: Get source operand (operand1)
                            Let src_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP1)

                            If result_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                If src_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                    Let result_type be __load(result_ptr, OP_TYPE)
                                    Let src_type be __load(src_ptr, OP_TYPE)

                                    Note: Both must be register operands
                                    If result_type equals OPERAND_REGISTER:
                                        If src_type equals OPERAND_REGISTER:
                                            Let result_reg be __load(result_ptr, OP_REG_ID)
                                            Let src_reg be __load(src_ptr, OP_REG_ID)

                                            Note: Same register - this move is redundant
                                            If result_reg equals src_reg:
                                                __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_NOP)
                                                Let eliminated_count be eliminated_count plus 1
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Let instr_idx be instr_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If

        Let block_idx be block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return eliminated_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pass 2: Strength-Reduce Multiply by Power of Two
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Replaces IMUL instructions where one operand is an immediate power of two with
equivalent SHL (shift left) instructions. Shifts are significantly faster than
multiplications on all x86_64 microarchitectures:
- IMUL has 3 cycle latency on modern cores (sometimes pipelined at 1/cycle)
- SHL has 1 cycle latency

Supported transformations:
  imul $1, %reg   -> NOP (identity, multiplication by 1)
  imul $2, %reg   -> shl $1, %reg
  imul $4, %reg   -> shl $2, %reg
  imul $8, %reg   -> shl $3, %reg
  imul $16, %reg  -> shl $4, %reg
  imul $32, %reg  -> shl $5, %reg
  imul $64, %reg  -> shl $6, %reg
  imul $128, %reg -> shl $7, %reg
  imul $256, %reg -> shl $8, %reg
  ... and any other power of two

The power-of-two test uses the bit trick: val > 0 && (val & (val - 1)) == 0.
The shift amount is computed by counting trailing zeros (log2 of the power).

We check operand2 for an immediate power-of-two value. The result operand and
operand1 are preserved, and the opcode is changed from LIR_IMUL to LIR_SHL.
The immediate value in operand2 is replaced with the shift amount.

Returns the number of strength reductions applied.
@End Reasoning

Process called "strength_reduce_multiply" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let reduced_count be 0

    Let blocks_ptr be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCKS)
    Let block_count be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCK_COUNT)

    If blocks_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If block_count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_idx be 0
    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be List.list_get(blocks_ptr, block_idx)
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instr_list be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS)
            Let instr_count be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT)

            If instr_list is not equal to 0:
                Let instr_idx be 0
                While instr_idx is less than instr_count:
                    Let instr be List.list_get(instr_list, instr_idx)
                    If instr is not equal to 0:
                        Let opcode be __load(instr, INSTR_OPCODE)

                        If opcode equals LIR_IMUL:
                            Note: Check if operand2 is an immediate
                            Let op2_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP2)
                            If op2_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                Let op2_type be __load(op2_ptr, OP_TYPE)

                                If op2_type equals OPERAND_IMMEDIATE:
                                    Let imm_value be __load(op2_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE)

                                    Note: Multiply by 1 is identity - convert to NOP
                                    If imm_value equals 1:
                                        __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_NOP)
                                        Let reduced_count be reduced_count plus 1
                                    Otherwise:
                                        Note: Check for power of two
                                        If is_power_of_two(imm_value) equals 1:
                                            Let shift_amount be log2_of_power(imm_value)

                                            Note: Replace IMUL with SHL
                                            __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_SHL)

                                            Note: Replace immediate value with shift amount
                                            __store(op2_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE, shift_amount)

                                            Let reduced_count be reduced_count plus 1
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Let instr_idx be instr_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If

        Let block_idx be block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return reduced_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pass 3: Optimize Zeroing Patterns
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Replaces MOV $0, %reg with XOR %reg, %reg. On x86_64, the XOR-with-self idiom
has two important advantages:

1. Shorter encoding: xorl %eax, %eax is 2 bytes versus movl $0, %eax which is
   5 bytes. Even though we operate on LIR (not raw bytes), the assembler will
   produce shorter code from the XOR form.

2. Dependency chain breaking: Modern x86_64 microarchitectures (Intel since
   Ivy Bridge, AMD since Zen) recognize XOR-with-self as a zeroing idiom and
   handle it in the rename stage without using an execution port. This breaks
   false dependencies on the previous value of the register.

The optimization only applies when:
- The instruction is LIR_MOV
- The source operand (operand1) is IMMEDIATE type with value 0
- The destination operand (result) is REGISTER type
- The operand size is 32 or 64 bits (XOR zeroing on 32-bit automatically
  zero-extends to 64-bit on x86_64)

The transformation replaces the opcode with LIR_XOR and sets both operand1 and
operand2 to register operands with the same register ID as the destination.

Returns the number of zeroing optimizations applied.
@End Reasoning

Process called "optimize_zeroing" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let zeroing_count be 0

    Let blocks_ptr be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCKS)
    Let block_count be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCK_COUNT)

    If blocks_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If block_count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_idx be 0
    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be List.list_get(blocks_ptr, block_idx)
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instr_list be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS)
            Let instr_count be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT)

            If instr_list is not equal to 0:
                Let instr_idx be 0
                While instr_idx is less than instr_count:
                    Let instr be List.list_get(instr_list, instr_idx)
                    If instr is not equal to 0:
                        Let opcode be __load(instr, INSTR_OPCODE)

                        If opcode equals LIR_MOV:
                            Note: Check if source operand is immediate 0
                            Let src_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP1)
                            Let result_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_RESULT)

                            If src_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                If result_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                    Let src_type be __load(src_ptr, OP_TYPE)
                                    Let result_type be __load(result_ptr, OP_TYPE)

                                    If src_type equals OPERAND_IMMEDIATE:
                                        If result_type equals OPERAND_REGISTER:
                                            Let imm_value be __load(src_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE)

                                            If imm_value equals 0:
                                                Note: Check operand size is 32 or 64 bits
                                                Let op_size be __load(result_ptr, OP_SIZE)

                                                If op_size equals 4:
                                                    Note: 32-bit operand, eligible
                                                    Let dest_reg be __load(result_ptr, OP_REG_ID)

                                                    Note: Change opcode to XOR
                                                    __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_XOR)

                                                    Note: Set operand1 to register operand with same reg
                                                    __store(src_ptr, OP_TYPE, OPERAND_REGISTER)
                                                    __store(src_ptr, OP_REG_ID, dest_reg)
                                                    __store(src_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE, 0)
                                                    __store(src_ptr, OP_SIZE, op_size)

                                                    Note: Create operand2 as register with same reg
                                                    Let op2_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP2)
                                                    If op2_ptr equals 0:
                                                        Note: Allocate a new operand for op2
                                                        Let new_op2 be Layout.allocate(64)
                                                        If new_op2 is not equal to 0:
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_TYPE, OPERAND_REGISTER)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_REG_ID, dest_reg)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_IMM_VALUE, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_BASE_REG, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_INDEX_REG, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_SCALE, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_DISP, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_SIZE, op_size)
                                                            __store(instr, INSTR_OP2, new_op2)
                                                        Otherwise:
                                                        __store(op2_ptr, OP_TYPE, OPERAND_REGISTER)
                                                        __store(op2_ptr, OP_REG_ID, dest_reg)
                                                        __store(op2_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE, 0)
                                                        __store(op2_ptr, OP_SIZE, op_size)
                                                    End If

                                                    Let zeroing_count be zeroing_count plus 1
                                                End If

                                                If op_size equals 8:
                                                    Note: 64-bit operand, eligible
                                                    Let dest_reg be __load(result_ptr, OP_REG_ID)

                                                    Note: Change opcode to XOR
                                                    __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_XOR)

                                                    Note: Set operand1 to register operand with same reg
                                                    __store(src_ptr, OP_TYPE, OPERAND_REGISTER)
                                                    __store(src_ptr, OP_REG_ID, dest_reg)
                                                    __store(src_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE, 0)
                                                    __store(src_ptr, OP_SIZE, op_size)

                                                    Note: Create or update operand2
                                                    Let op2_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP2)
                                                    If op2_ptr equals 0:
                                                        Let new_op2 be Layout.allocate(64)
                                                        If new_op2 is not equal to 0:
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_TYPE, OPERAND_REGISTER)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_REG_ID, dest_reg)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_IMM_VALUE, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_BASE_REG, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_INDEX_REG, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_SCALE, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_DISP, 0)
                                                            __store(new_op2, OP_SIZE, op_size)
                                                            __store(instr, INSTR_OP2, new_op2)
                                                        Otherwise:
                                                        __store(op2_ptr, OP_TYPE, OPERAND_REGISTER)
                                                        __store(op2_ptr, OP_REG_ID, dest_reg)
                                                        __store(op2_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE, 0)
                                                        __store(op2_ptr, OP_SIZE, op_size)
                                                    End If

                                                    Let zeroing_count be zeroing_count plus 1
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Let instr_idx be instr_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If

        Let block_idx be block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return zeroing_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pass 4: Optimize INC/DEC Patterns
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Replaces ADD $1, %reg with INC %reg, SUB $1, %reg with DEC %reg,
ADD $-1, %reg with DEC %reg, and SUB $-1, %reg with INC %reg.

INC and DEC are slightly more compact in encoding (1-2 bytes shorter) and
express intent more clearly. On modern x86_64 microarchitectures, INC/DEC
have the same latency as ADD/SUB but use fewer instruction bytes, improving
instruction cache density.

Note that INC/DEC do NOT update the carry flag (CF), while ADD/SUB do. This
optimization is safe as long as the carry flag is not read between this
instruction and the next instruction that sets flags. In LIR, we track flag
usage explicitly, so this transformation is safe within basic blocks where
flag liveness is known.

The transformation modifies the instruction in-place:
- Changes opcode to LIR_INC or LIR_DEC
- The result operand (destination register) is preserved
- The operand1 (source register) is preserved for the unary operation
- The operand2 (immediate $1 or $-1) is no longer needed

Returns the number of INC/DEC optimizations applied.
@End Reasoning

Process called "optimize_inc_dec" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let opt_count be 0

    Let blocks_ptr be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCKS)
    Let block_count be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCK_COUNT)

    If blocks_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If block_count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_idx be 0
    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be List.list_get(blocks_ptr, block_idx)
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instr_list be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS)
            Let instr_count be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT)

            If instr_list is not equal to 0:
                Let instr_idx be 0
                While instr_idx is less than instr_count:
                    Let instr be List.list_get(instr_list, instr_idx)
                    If instr is not equal to 0:
                        Let opcode be __load(instr, INSTR_OPCODE)

                        Note: Check ADD instructions
                        If opcode equals LIR_ADD:
                            Let op2_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP2)
                            If op2_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                Let op2_type be __load(op2_ptr, OP_TYPE)
                                If op2_type equals OPERAND_IMMEDIATE:
                                    Let imm_value be __load(op2_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE)

                                    Note: ADD $1, %reg -> INC %reg
                                    If imm_value equals 1:
                                        __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_INC)
                                        __store(instr, INSTR_OP2, 0)
                                        Let opt_count be opt_count plus 1
                                    End If

                                    Note: ADD $-1, %reg -> DEC %reg
                                    If imm_value equals 0 minus 1:
                                        __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_DEC)
                                        __store(instr, INSTR_OP2, 0)
                                        Let opt_count be opt_count plus 1
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If

                        Note: Check SUB instructions
                        If opcode equals LIR_SUB:
                            Let op2_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP2)
                            If op2_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                Let op2_type be __load(op2_ptr, OP_TYPE)
                                If op2_type equals OPERAND_IMMEDIATE:
                                    Let imm_value be __load(op2_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE)

                                    Note: SUB $1, %reg -> DEC %reg
                                    If imm_value equals 1:
                                        __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_DEC)
                                        __store(instr, INSTR_OP2, 0)
                                        Let opt_count be opt_count plus 1
                                    End If

                                    Note: SUB $-1, %reg -> INC %reg
                                    If imm_value equals 0 minus 1:
                                        __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_INC)
                                        __store(instr, INSTR_OP2, 0)
                                        Let opt_count be opt_count plus 1
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Let instr_idx be instr_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If

        Let block_idx be block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return opt_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pass 5: Eliminate Dead Stores
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Scans pairs of adjacent instructions within each basic block. If instruction I
writes to a register R and the immediately following instruction I+1 also writes
to register R, and I+1 does NOT read R in any of its source operands, then the
write in instruction I is dead (its result is never consumed). In that case,
instruction I is replaced with NOP.

This is a conservative local analysis: we only consider adjacent instruction pairs
within a single basic block. Cross-block dead store elimination requires full
liveness analysis, which is handled by a separate pass (liveness.runa).

The reason we check that I+1 does not read R is that in two-operand form
instructions (e.g., ADD %rax, %rbx where %rax is both read and written), the
destination register is also an implicit source. If I+1 reads R, then I's write
is still live.

Returns the number of dead stores eliminated.
@End Reasoning

Process called "eliminate_dead_stores" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let eliminated_count be 0

    Let blocks_ptr be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCKS)
    Let block_count be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCK_COUNT)

    If blocks_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If block_count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_idx be 0
    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be List.list_get(blocks_ptr, block_idx)
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instr_list be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS)
            Let instr_count be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT)

            If instr_list is not equal to 0:
                Note: Need at least 2 instructions to compare adjacent pairs
                If instr_count is greater than or equal to 2:
                    Let instr_idx be 0
                    Let limit be instr_count minus 1

                    While instr_idx is less than limit:
                        Let current_instr be List.list_get(instr_list, instr_idx)
                        Let next_instr be List.list_get(instr_list, instr_idx plus 1)

                        If current_instr is not equal to 0:
                            If next_instr is not equal to 0:
                                Let curr_opcode be __load(current_instr, INSTR_OPCODE)
                                Let next_opcode be __load(next_instr, INSTR_OPCODE)

                                Note: Skip if current is already NOP or a non-writing instruction
                                If instruction_writes_register(curr_opcode) equals 1:
                                    Note: Check if next instruction also writes a register
                                    If instruction_writes_register(next_opcode) equals 1:
                                        Let curr_dest_reg be get_result_register(current_instr)
                                        Let next_dest_reg be get_result_register(next_instr)

                                        Note: Both write to the same register
                                        If curr_dest_reg is not equal to 0 minus 1:
                                            If curr_dest_reg equals next_dest_reg:
                                                Note: Verify next instruction does NOT read
                                                Note: the same register in its source operands
                                                If instruction_reads_register(next_instr, curr_dest_reg) equals 0:
                                                    Note: The write in current_instr is dead
                                                    __store(current_instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_NOP)
                                                    Let eliminated_count be eliminated_count plus 1
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If

                        Let instr_idx be instr_idx plus 1
                    End While
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Let block_idx be block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return eliminated_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pass 6: Thread Jumps
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
When a JMP instruction targets a basic block whose only content is another JMP,
the first JMP can be redirected to the ultimate target, bypassing the trivial
intermediate block. This eliminates unnecessary control flow indirection.

The algorithm walks jump chains up to 10 levels deep to handle cascaded trivial
blocks (block A jumps to B which jumps to C which jumps to D...) while also
preventing infinite loops from cycles in the control flow graph.

A block is considered "trivial" (a forwarding block) if:
1. It contains exactly one instruction
2. That instruction is an unconditional JMP (opcode 30500)

For each JMP instruction in the function, we resolve its target block and check
whether that block is trivial. If so, we follow the chain until we find a
non-trivial target or exhaust the depth limit.

The JMP target is stored in operand1 as the target block ID. We look up blocks
by iterating the function's block list and matching block IDs.

Returns the number of jumps threaded.
@End Reasoning

Process called "thread_jumps" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let threaded_count be 0

    Let blocks_ptr be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCKS)
    Let block_count be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCK_COUNT)

    If blocks_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If block_count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_idx be 0
    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be List.list_get(blocks_ptr, block_idx)
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instr_list be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS)
            Let instr_count be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT)

            If instr_list is not equal to 0:
                Let instr_idx be 0
                While instr_idx is less than instr_count:
                    Let instr be List.list_get(instr_list, instr_idx)
                    If instr is not equal to 0:
                        Let opcode be __load(instr, INSTR_OPCODE)

                        If opcode equals LIR_JMP:
                            Note: Get the target block ID from operand1
                            Let op1_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP1)
                            If op1_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                Let op1_type be __load(op1_ptr, OP_TYPE)
                                If op1_type equals OPERAND_IMMEDIATE:
                                    Let target_block_id be __load(op1_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE)
                                    Let original_target be target_block_id

                                    Note: Walk the jump chain up to 10 levels deep
                                    Let chain_depth be 0
                                    Let chain_max be 10
                                    Let keep_following be 1

                                    While keep_following equals 1:
                                        If chain_depth is greater than or equal to chain_max:
                                            Let keep_following be 0
                                        Otherwise:
                                            Note: Find the target block by scanning the block list
                                            Let target_block be find_block_by_id(blocks_ptr, block_count, target_block_id)

                                            If target_block equals 0:
                                                Note: Target block not found, stop following
                                                Let keep_following be 0
                                            Otherwise:
                                                Note: Check if target block is trivial (single JMP)
                                                Let target_instr_list be __load(target_block, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS)
                                                Let target_instr_count be __load(target_block, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT)

                                                If target_instr_count equals 1:
                                                    If target_instr_list is not equal to 0:
                                                        Let target_instr be List.list_get(target_instr_list, 0)
                                                        If target_instr is not equal to 0:
                                                            Let target_opcode be __load(target_instr, INSTR_OPCODE)
                                                            If target_opcode equals LIR_JMP:
                                                                Note: This is a trivial forwarding block
                                                                Let target_op1 be __load(target_instr, INSTR_OP1)
                                                                If target_op1 is not equal to 0:
                                                                    Let target_op1_type be __load(target_op1, OP_TYPE)
                                                                    If target_op1_type equals OPERAND_IMMEDIATE:
                                                                        Let next_target be __load(target_op1, OP_IMM_VALUE)

                                                                        Note: Avoid self-loops
                                                                        If next_target equals target_block_id:
                                                                            Let keep_following be 0
                                                                        Otherwise:
                                                                            Let target_block_id be next_target
                                                                            Let chain_depth be chain_depth plus 1
                                                                        Otherwise:
                                                                        Let keep_following be 0
                                                                    Otherwise:
                                                                    Let keep_following be 0
                                                                Otherwise:
                                                                Note: Not a JMP, stop following
                                                                Let keep_following be 0
                                                            Otherwise:
                                                            Let keep_following be 0
                                                        Otherwise:
                                                        Let keep_following be 0
                                                    Otherwise:
                                                    Note: Block has multiple instructions, not trivial
                                                    Let keep_following be 0
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End While

                                    Note: If target changed, update the JMP operand
                                    If target_block_id is not equal to original_target:
                                        __store(op1_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE, target_block_id)
                                        Let threaded_count be threaded_count plus 1
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Let instr_idx be instr_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If

        Let block_idx be block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return threaded_count
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper to find a basic block by its block_id within the function's block list.
Performs a linear scan since block lists are typically small (tens to hundreds
of blocks per function). Returns the block pointer if found, 0 if not found.
@End Reasoning

Process called "find_block_by_id" that takes blocks_ptr as Integer, block_count as Integer, target_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If blocks_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be List.list_get(blocks_ptr, idx)
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let block_id be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_ID)
            If block_id equals target_id:
                Return block_ptr
            End If
        End If
        Let idx be idx plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pass 7: Fold Constant Operations
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
If both operands of an arithmetic or logical instruction are immediate constants,
we can evaluate the operation at compile time and replace the instruction with a
MOV of the computed result into the destination register.

Supported operations for constant folding:
- ADD: result = op1 + op2
- SUB: result = op1 - op2
- AND: result = op1 & op2
- OR:  result = op1 | op2
- XOR: result = op1 ^ op2
- SHL: result = op1 << op2 (with shift amount bounds check)
- SHR: result = op1 >> op2 (logical shift, with bounds check)

The transformation replaces the instruction opcode with LIR_MOV and sets
operand1 to an immediate operand carrying the computed result value. Operand2
is cleared (set to 0).

For shift operations, the shift amount is clamped to 0-63 to prevent undefined
behavior on x86_64 (which masks shift amounts to 6 bits for 64-bit operands).

Returns the number of constant operations folded.
@End Reasoning

Process called "fold_constant_operations" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let folded_count be 0

    Let blocks_ptr be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCKS)
    Let block_count be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCK_COUNT)

    If blocks_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If block_count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_idx be 0
    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be List.list_get(blocks_ptr, block_idx)
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instr_list be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS)
            Let instr_count be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT)

            If instr_list is not equal to 0:
                Let instr_idx be 0
                While instr_idx is less than instr_count:
                    Let instr be List.list_get(instr_list, instr_idx)
                    If instr is not equal to 0:
                        Let opcode be __load(instr, INSTR_OPCODE)

                        Note: Only fold binary operations that take two operands
                        Let is_foldable be 0
                        If opcode equals LIR_ADD:
                            Let is_foldable be 1
                        End If
                        If opcode equals LIR_SUB:
                            Let is_foldable be 1
                        End If
                        If opcode equals LIR_AND:
                            Let is_foldable be 1
                        End If
                        If opcode equals LIR_OR:
                            Let is_foldable be 1
                        End If
                        If opcode equals LIR_XOR:
                            Let is_foldable be 1
                        End If
                        If opcode equals LIR_SHL:
                            Let is_foldable be 1
                        End If
                        If opcode equals LIR_SHR:
                            Let is_foldable be 1
                        End If

                        If is_foldable equals 1:
                            Let op1_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP1)
                            Let op2_ptr be __load(instr, INSTR_OP2)

                            If op1_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                If op2_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                    Let op1_type be __load(op1_ptr, OP_TYPE)
                                    Let op2_type be __load(op2_ptr, OP_TYPE)

                                    Note: Both operands must be immediates
                                    If op1_type equals OPERAND_IMMEDIATE:
                                        If op2_type equals OPERAND_IMMEDIATE:
                                            Let val1 be __load(op1_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE)
                                            Let val2 be __load(op2_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE)
                                            Let result_value be 0
                                            Let fold_valid be 1

                                            If opcode equals LIR_ADD:
                                                Let result_value be val1 plus val2
                                            End If

                                            If opcode equals LIR_SUB:
                                                Let result_value be val1 minus val2
                                            End If

                                            If opcode equals LIR_AND:
                                                Let result_value be val1 & val2
                                            End If

                                            If opcode equals LIR_OR:
                                                Let result_value be val1 | val2
                                            End If

                                            If opcode equals LIR_XOR:
                                                Let result_value be val1 ^ val2
                                            End If

                                            If opcode equals LIR_SHL:
                                                Note: Clamp shift amount to 0-63
                                                Let shift_amt be val2
                                                If shift_amt is less than 0:
                                                    Let fold_valid be 0
                                                Otherwise:
                                                    If shift_amt is greater than 63:
                                                        Let shift_amt be 63
                                                    End If
                                                    Note: Compute shift using iterative doubling
                                                    Let result_value be val1
                                                    Let shift_i be 0
                                                    While shift_i is less than shift_amt:
                                                        Let result_value be result_value multiplied by 2
                                                        Let shift_i be shift_i plus 1
                                                    End While
                                                End If
                                            End If

                                            If opcode equals LIR_SHR:
                                                Note: Clamp shift amount to 0-63 (logical shift right)
                                                Let shift_amt be val2
                                                If shift_amt is less than 0:
                                                    Let fold_valid be 0
                                                Otherwise:
                                                    If shift_amt is greater than 63:
                                                        Let shift_amt be 63
                                                    End If
                                                    Note: Compute logical shift right using iterative halving
                                                    Let result_value be val1
                                                    Let shift_i be 0
                                                    While shift_i is less than shift_amt:
                                                        Let result_value be result_value divided by 2
                                                        Let shift_i be shift_i plus 1
                                                    End While
                                                End If
                                            End If

                                            If fold_valid equals 1:
                                                Note: Replace instruction with MOV $result, %dest
                                                __store(instr, INSTR_OPCODE, LIR_MOV)

                                                Note: Set operand1 to the computed immediate result
                                                __store(op1_ptr, OP_TYPE, OPERAND_IMMEDIATE)
                                                __store(op1_ptr, OP_IMM_VALUE, result_value)

                                                Note: Clear operand2
                                                __store(instr, INSTR_OP2, 0)

                                                Let folded_count be folded_count plus 1
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Let instr_idx be instr_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If

        Let block_idx be block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return folded_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pass 8: Remove NOPs
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Final cleanup pass that removes all NOP instructions from every basic block's
instruction list. Previous passes (redundant move elimination, strength reduction
with identity case, dead store elimination) convert eliminated instructions to
NOPs rather than removing them in-place, because removing from a list during
iteration invalidates indices and causes skipped or double-processed entries.

This pass performs the actual removal by building a new instruction list for each
block containing only the non-NOP instructions, then replacing the block's
instruction list with the compacted one. After compaction, instruction indices
are renumbered sequentially starting from 0.

Returns the total number of NOP instructions removed across all blocks.
@End Reasoning

Process called "remove_nops" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let removed_count be 0

    Let blocks_ptr be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCKS)
    Let block_count be __load(lir_function, FUNC_BLOCK_COUNT)

    If blocks_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If block_count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_idx be 0
    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be List.list_get(blocks_ptr, block_idx)
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instr_list be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS)
            Let instr_count be __load(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT)

            If instr_list is not equal to 0:
                Note: Count how many NOPs exist in this block
                Let nop_count be 0
                Let scan_idx be 0
                While scan_idx is less than instr_count:
                    Let scan_instr be List.list_get(instr_list, scan_idx)
                    If scan_instr is not equal to 0:
                        Let scan_opcode be __load(scan_instr, INSTR_OPCODE)
                        If scan_opcode equals LIR_NOP:
                            Let nop_count be nop_count plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    Let scan_idx be scan_idx plus 1
                End While

                Note: Only rebuild the list if there are NOPs to remove
                If nop_count is greater than 0:
                    Let new_list be List.list_create()
                    If new_list is not equal to 0:
                        Let new_index be 0
                        Let copy_idx be 0

                        While copy_idx is less than instr_count:
                            Let copy_instr be List.list_get(instr_list, copy_idx)
                            If copy_instr is not equal to 0:
                                Let copy_opcode be __load(copy_instr, INSTR_OPCODE)
                                If copy_opcode is not equal to LIR_NOP:
                                    Note: Renumber the instruction index
                                    __store(copy_instr, INSTR_INDEX, new_index)

                                    Note: Add to new list
                                    List.list_push(new_list, copy_instr)
                                    Let new_index be new_index plus 1
                                End If
                            End If
                            Let copy_idx be copy_idx plus 1
                        End While

                        Note: Update block to use the new compacted instruction list
                        __store(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTRUCTIONS, new_list)
                        __store(block_ptr, BLOCK_INSTR_COUNT, new_index)

                        Note: Update the linked list 'next' pointers for remaining instructions
                        Let link_idx be 0
                        Let new_count be List.list_length(new_list)
                        While link_idx is less than new_count:
                            Let link_instr be List.list_get(new_list, link_idx)
                            If link_instr is not equal to 0:
                                If link_idx is less than new_count minus 1:
                                    Let next_instr be List.list_get(new_list, link_idx plus 1)
                                    __store(link_instr, INSTR_NEXT, next_instr)
                                Otherwise:
                                    Note: Last instruction has no next
                                    __store(link_instr, INSTR_NEXT, 0)
                                End If
                            End If
                            Let link_idx be link_idx plus 1
                        End While

                        Let removed_count be removed_count plus nop_count
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Let block_idx be block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return removed_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Statistics Query Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Provides accessor functions for reading individual fields from an
OptimizationStats structure. These allow callers to query specific optimization
counts without needing to know the internal memory layout.
@End Reasoning

Process called "stats_get_redundant_moves" that takes stats as Integer returns Integer:
    If stats equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(stats, STATS_REDUNDANT_MOVES)
End Process

Process called "stats_get_strength_reductions" that takes stats as Integer returns Integer:
    If stats equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(stats, STATS_STRENGTH_REDUCTIONS)
End Process

Process called "stats_get_zeroing_optimizations" that takes stats as Integer returns Integer:
    If stats equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(stats, STATS_ZEROING)
End Process

Process called "stats_get_inc_dec_optimizations" that takes stats as Integer returns Integer:
